<br>
I also leave for Peru tomorrow afternoon.  This includes a ten-hour flight and the normal swelling of the feet, not to mention walking around cities, Machu Picchu, and up and down the Andes mountains.<br>
<br>
I also smacked the same toe into a chair again this evening, and heard yet another little &quot;snick&quot; sound.<br>
<br>
Grrr.......!!!!  This is the fourteenth bone I've broken!  (Another fun little thing here...  yes, I've broken 14 bones.  Only two of them were mine.  The rest, bear in mind, were COMPLETE accidents!  They include breking my mother's tailbone when I was born, and my sister's fingers, another of my sister's fingers, my sister's hand, my sister's foot, my sister's leg...  Yes, the girl needs to drink some milk. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
So...  stories of broken bones.  What was the most painful?  The most inconvenient?  The biggest bone you've broken?<br>
<br>
Discuss. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 889<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/6/02 7:48:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken</span><hr size=1> I was at a water park once when I was 10, and went down this long slide head first.  I'm zoomin along at mach speeds, and up ahead this great big woman is sittin up as she's going down the slide, movin at like 0.5 mph. <br>
<br>
I managed to zoom right under her bottom (seriously) and almost drowned.  Fortunately I didn't hit her until almost the very bottom of the slide so we both finally fell off the thing.  I prolly coulda won grand prize on America's funniest home videos had someone caught it on tape.<br>
